com.dlsc.flexgantt.command.treetable

Class DefaultDeleteMultipleNodesCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.dlsc.flexgantt.command.AbstractCommand
      • com.dlsc.flexgantt.command.AbstractCompoundCommand<DefaultDeleteNodeCommand>
        • com.dlsc.flexgantt.command.treetable.DefaultDeleteMultipleNodesCommand
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICommand, Serializable

    public class DefaultDeleteMultipleNodesCommand
extends AbstractCompoundCommand<DefaultDeleteNodeCommand>
    A command that deletes several tree table nodes from the model at the same time. This command can only be used in situations where the tree table model is an instance of DefaultTreeTableModel and the deleted child nodes and their parent nodes are all implementors of the IMutableTreeTableNode interface.
